Currently when there is any change on the repositories in Fisheye, there is a need to manually refresh the cache in JIRA. This information is available in this [page|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Integrating+JIRA+with+FishEye]:
{quote}
*JIRA requires FishEye to manually refresh repository cache when repository changes are made* — When a repository is removed, or when there has been any change in FishEye repositories, JIRA does not update the FishEye repository list cache automatically. You must manually refresh the repository list cache. This is done in JIRA: 'Administration' > 'FishEye Configuration' > 'Refresh Cache' link (next to 'Repository List Cache').
{quote}

However, we've seen many support cases where the customer is not aware of this procedure. I believe we would be able to avoid some of them if we make this information more visible in our documentation.

